cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper deals with image processing, specifically biomedical image processing, and proposes a new prior based on the gradient distribution of natural-scene images. This makes it highly likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also involves optimization problems and efficient solver algorithms, which suggests it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), or signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
